3:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Funding rates are calculated hourly based on the 8-hour TWAP of the premium index between Aevo's TON perp price and spot reference. Payments occur every hour at the top of each hour, with rates typically ranging from -0.5% to +2% during high volatility periods. The off-chain order book provides real-time price discovery while the rollup ensures deterministic funding rate execution without MEV interference."}]
4:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","TON","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"TON's Layer 1 status and integration with Telegram creates unique funding patterns driven by ecosystem developments and user adoption cycles. The pair often exhibits sustained positive funding during TON ecosystem announcements, making it attractive for arbitrageurs willing to short perpetuals against spot holdings."}]]}]
5:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"TON/USDT funding on Aevo has shown distinct patterns correlating with Telegram integration milestones and DeFi protocol launches on TON. During Q3 2024, rates averaged +0.15% hourly during ecosystem expansion phases, with spikes to +1.8% during major partnership announcements. The rollup's 1-hour intervals capture intraday sentiment shifts more granularly than 8-hour systems. Negative funding periods typically coincide with broader L1 token rotation, offering opportunities for long perpetual positions against short spot exposure."}]]}]
6:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunities and Execution"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"The combination of Aevo's pre-launch token markets and established TON perpetuals creates cross-product arbitrage opportunities beyond simple funding rate trades. Traders can exploit funding rate differentials by maintaining delta-neutral positions using TON spot on centralized exchanges while collecting positive funding on Aevo. The rollup's performance advantage reduces slippage during position adjustments, though liquidity depth remains lower than major CEXs. Optimal position sizing typically ranges from $10K-$100K to avoid moving the market significantly."}]]}]
7:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Considerations and Mitigation"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Aevo's rollup introduces smart contract risk and potential centralization concerns around the sequencer, requiring careful position monitoring during network upgrades. The smaller liquidity pool means funding rates can be more volatile than established exchanges, creating both opportunity and liquidation risk. Counterparty risk differs from CEXs as funds remain in smart contracts rather than exchange custody, but this requires users to understand rollup withdrawal mechanisms. Position limits and automated hedging become critical given the 1-hour funding frequency and potential for rapid rate changes during TON ecosystem volatility."}]]}]
8:["$","$Ld",null,{"items":[{"question":"How does Aevo's rollup affect TON/USDT funding rate reliability?","answer":"The rollup provides deterministic execution and reduces MEV manipulation of funding rates. However, the sequencer dependency means funding calculations could be delayed during rollup maintenance, though historical uptime exceeds 99.8%."},{"question":"What's the minimum position size for effective TON funding arbitrage on Aevo?","answer":"Given Aevo's 0.02% maker fees and typical funding rates, positions below $5,000 often result in negative returns after gas and transaction costs. Optimal sizing starts around $10,000 for meaningful profit capture."},{"question":"Can I use Aevo's options alongside TON perpetuals for enhanced arbitrage?","answer":"Yes, Aevo's options market allows for sophisticated strategies combining funding rate collection with volatility trades. Selling TON calls while long perpetuals can enhance returns during high funding periods, though this adds complexity and Greeks exposure."},{"question":"How do TON ecosystem events impact funding rates on Aevo specifically?","answer":"Aevo's pre-launch markets often signal TON ecosystem developments early, leading to funding rate changes before other exchanges. Major Telegram integrations or DeFi launches typically drive 24-48 hours of elevated positive funding as speculation increases."}]}]
